{"hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc:\/\/net.doo.ScanbotSDK\/documentation\/ScanbotSDK","doc:\/\/net.doo.ScanbotSDK\/documentation\/ScanbotSDK\/SBSDKBaseScannerEnergyConfiguration"]]},"abstract":[{"text":"If enabled the idle timer of the device will be disabled while the scanner is active, preventing the device from going to sleep (dim and lock screen).","type":"text"}],"metadata":{"roleHeading":"Instance Property","externalID":"c:@M@ScanbotSDK@objc(cs)SBSDKBaseScannerEnergyConfiguration(py)keepScreenOn","role":"symbol","fragments":[{"text":"var","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"keepScreenOn","kind":"identifier"},{"text":": ","kind":"text"},{"preciseIdentifier":"s:Sb","text":"Bool","kind":"typeIdentifier"}],"navigatorTitle":[{"text":"keepScreenOn","kind":"identifier"}],"title":"keepScreenOn","symbolKind":"property","modules":[{"name":"ScanbotSDK"}]},"variants":[{"paths":["\/documentation\/scanbotsdk\/sbsdkbasescannerenergyconfiguration\/keepscreenon"],"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"swift"}]},{"paths":["\/documentation\/scanbotsdk\/sbsdkbasescannerenergyconfiguration\/keepscreenon"],"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"occ"}]}],"schemaVersion":{"major":0,"minor":3,"patch":0},"sections":[],"primaryContentSections":[{"kind":"declarations","declarations":[{"languages":["swift"],"tokens":[{"text":"@objc","kind":"attribute"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"dynamic","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"var","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"keepScreenOn","kind":"identifier"},{"text":": ","kind":"text"},{"text":"Bool","kind":"typeIdentifier","preciseIdentifier":"s:Sb"},{"text":" { ","kind":"text"},{"text":"get","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"set","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" }","kind":"text"}],"platforms":["iOS"]}]}],"kind":"symbol","identifier":{"url":"doc:\/\/net.doo.ScanbotSDK\/documentation\/ScanbotSDK\/SBSDKBaseScannerEnergyConfiguration\/keepScreenOn","interfaceLanguage":"swift"},"references":{"doc://net.doo.ScanbotSDK/documentation/ScanbotSDK":{"identifier":"doc:\/\/net.doo.ScanbotSDK\/documentation\/ScanbotSDK","url":"\/documentation\/scanbotsdk","title":"ScanbotSDK","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Version: 8.0.2"}],"kind":"symbol","type":"topic","role":"collection"},"doc://net.doo.ScanbotSDK/documentation/ScanbotSDK/SBSDKBaseScannerEnergyConfiguration":{"abstract":[{"text":"The energy management configuration object for a ‘SBSDKBaseScannerViewController’ and its subclasses.","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"‘SBSDKBaseScannerViewController’ and subclasses sport a customizable energy management system.","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"Since scanners running on a live video feed can put a lot of load onto the CPU and\/or GPU","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"of the device, causing the battery to drain quickly and running the device hot, you can customize the energy","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"consumption using this class by configuring the rate of detections\/recognitions per second in performance mode as"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"well as in energy saving mode."},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"In performance mode the scanners will be fed with a higher, configurable rate of","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"video frames per second.","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"After a certain, configurable period of inactivity the energy save mode will be engaged and the rate","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"of scans will be reduced to a lower (configurable) rate.","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"You can also configure the time of inactivity before the automatic mode switches from performance to energy save mode.","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"Inactivity here means that both of the following conditions are met:"}],"identifier":"doc:\/\/net